did.abstract: The Miller, N mss. II consists of the manuscripts, teaching materials, correspondence, journals, and other materials of writer Nolan Miller.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.
Many collections are housed offsite; retrieval requires advance notice. Please make an appointment a minimum of one week in advance of your visit.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Nolan Miller (1907-2006) was a author, editor of The Antioch Review, and professor of English at Antioch College in Ohio. He has published four novels and various short stories over several decades.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged into the following series: I. Novels, II. Unpublished Novels, III. Miscellaneous Novel Drafts, IV. Short Stories, V. Other Writings, VI. Journals, VII. Correspondence, VIII. Teaching Materials, IX. Miscellaneous

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: I. Novels contains manuscripts of Miller's published novels The Merry Innocents, A Moth of Time, and Why Am I So Beat?. II. Unpublished Novels contains the manuscripts for Miller's unpublished novels and novellas. III. Miscellaneous Novel Drafts includes various drafts, exerpts, and parts of novels. IV. Short Stories contain manuscripts of Miller's extensive short stories. V. Other Writings includes Miller's drafts of his autobiography, the Living Language textbook, poetry, short plays, and other pieces of fiction and nonfiction writings. VI. Journals includes the journals of Miller from 1942 to 1963. VII. Correspondence consists of letters to and from Miller from 1944-1991. VIII. Teaching Materials includes various workshops, lectures, evaluations, and other materials related to Miller's time at Antioch College. IX. Miscellaneous includes all other items, including photos, clippings, notes, notebooks, and periodicals containing Miller's publications.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Material
relatedmaterial.p: See Miller, N mss., also located at the Lilly Library, Indiana University, Bloomington, Indiana.
